    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nRunning  `carray_iteration` fails with C compilation error when shared utility is used:\n```\ncarray_iteration.c: In function ‘__pyx_memoryview_check’:\ncarray_iteration.c:12642:61: error: ‘__pyx_mstatetype’ has no member named ‘__pyx_memoryview_type’\n12642 |   __pyx_t_1 = __Pyx_TypeCheck(__pyx_v_o, __pyx_mstate_global->__pyx_memoryview_type);\n```\n\nSteps to reproduce:\n\n1. Use branch from #7479 PR\n2. Run test with shared utility enabled: ` python runtests.py --no-fork --shared-utility --no-capture --no-cpp carray_iteration`\n\nTest fails with C compilation error mentioned above.\n\nNote: regular test without `--shared-utility` is passes without issue.\n\n> UPDATE:\n> Much simpler reproducer is:\n> ```\n> import cython\n> \n> @cython.cfunc\n> def main(a: cython.pointer[int]):\n >    pass\n> ```\n> \n> Compiling using shared utility enabled casues C compilation to fail with mentioned error.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "From the test log, it's not just that test but several test files, also shorter ones from the documentation like `restaurant` or `wrapper_class`. When I run those tests without the shared module then it does not generate this type check.",
