            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for investigating this.\n\nI wonder if the problem is already in  `AnnotationNode.analyse_type_annotation()`. We're calling `arg_type = annotation.analyse_as_type(env)` there, so we should know the declared type at that point. But then, we call `annotation.analyse_pytyping_modifiers()` and mess it up. Maybe that's the problem? Why do we keep looking for modifiers when we've already extracted a proper type from the annotation?\n",
